            <description><![CDATA[<h3>1.0.1-beta.3: Enhanced Precision & Localization</h3>

<p><strong>New Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Localization:</strong> Added a localization string catalog and
    integrated translatable languages into the project.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Layout Reset Recovery:</strong> Improved the reset process to
    automatically recover missing control items and recreate dividers by
    toggling the always-hidden section.
  </li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Improvements & Fixes:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Apple Menu Protection:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Added a target-relative guard band for macOS 14/15 and maintained
        AX-based guards for macOS 26+ to prevent accidental triggers.
      </li>

      <li>
        Included extra padding to keep move events clear of the Apple menu
        region.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Icon Management:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Simplified temporary item placement to anchor reliably to the left of
        the Thaw icon, dropping fragile bounds calculations.
      </li>

      <li>
        Ensured first-run or reset items remain hidden and do not leave blank
        icon slots.
      </li>

      <li>
        New menu bar items are now relocated correctly during the first cache
        pass.
      </li>

      <li>
        The image cache is now fully cleared during a layout reset to prevent
        stale icons.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>System Stability:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cursor Watchdog:</strong> Added an auto-show watchdog with a
        2-second timeout to recover the pointer if it becomes stuck hidden.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Move Reliability:</strong> Thaw now refreshes menu bar bounds
        before moves and retries if window IDs are stale.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Concurrency:</strong> Updated internal semaphores to be
        cancellation-safe, ensuring move/click paths always signal even if
        interrupted.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>UI Refinement:</strong> Removed overlay text during layout moves
    while maintaining the dim state for a cleaner look.
  </li>
</ul>
]]></description>
