            <description><![CDATA[<h3>1.0.1-beta.2: Layout Stability & Performance</h3>
<p><strong>New Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Layout Reset:</strong> Added a new reset button with a confirmation
    prompt to restore a fresh menu bar layout, automatically moving items to the
    "Hidden" section.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Empty State Feedback:</strong> The Ice Bar now correctly displays
    empty-state text when the "Hidden" or "Always-Hidden" sections have no
    items.
  </li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Improvements & Fixes:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Smoother Dragging:</strong> Stabilized the "fast drag" experience
    with improved retry logic and overlays to prevent icon gaps or "bounce-back"
    during reorganization.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Enhanced Caching:</strong> Thaw now prewarms item and image caches
    on startup and before opening the layout pane, significantly reducing
    loading delays for the Ice Bar.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Reliable Rendering:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Improved layout resets to use a two-pass mechanism and cache clearing to
        prevent stale icons from appearing.
      </li>
      <li>
        Icons now remain reliably visible immediately after layout moves or
        resets.
      </li>
      <li>
        Softened the initial Ice Bar loading state to prevent error flashes
        during the first render.
      </li>
      <li>
        Refined icon height clamping using status bar thickness fallbacks for
        more consistent sizing.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Error Handling:</strong> Replaced endless loading states with clear
    error messages if a layout timeout occurs.
  </li>
</ul>
]]></description>
